		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=436169"><span id="Scholar">Sianu</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />73 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Sianu&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Speaking as a level 52 wizard. <br /> <br />I believe the Rogue is better sustained dps.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't need to see the figures - I'd rather spend the time gaining xp and better spells : ) <br /> <br />That said, I was in an LDON last night, group of 6, and with KEI I only fell below 40% mana twice.  One of those times was when we faced 4 mobs at once.  We did have a chanter, a warrior and a cleric.  Chanter died at one point when the mobs resisted mez 3x.  I should add that I was the highest and the others 47-51, so it was easy for me.  I nuked 2 or 3 times on most mobs.  I have Improved Damage III on my Robe of Tempest.  My nukes all landed for 630-1300 depending which nuke I was using.  I did not have to evac, although groups generally like having evac in LDONs.  Saving the time to run back to the zone can make the difference in winning an LDON. <br /> <br />A couple more points to bear in mind:  Rogues are JUST dps and possibly pull.  Rogues also need to run to the mob, identify the right mob &amp; target it (wizards can be medding while we target and while others get the mob to 10% [edit LOL I mean down 10%, to 90% where I start casting]).  Wizards have many other features that someone who doesn't play one won't know.  Porting to zone and home again later is popular, and there are zones you can't get to without a friendly wizard/druid (granted, you can pay a stranger 2kpp, but then you have a max group of 5).  We also have roots that at some levels can be better than a druid.  We can snare and/or stun.  A good wizard will know how to keep one or 2 adds off them.  We can levitate others.  We have a nice range of self buffs.  Playing a wizard is more of a challenge and we really do need KEI, and bardsong helps as well.  In fact a bard's manasong can cut down the medding time a lot.  I have seen 2 wizards handle 5 mobs with no enchanter, shaman, bard or druid in the group.  I don't tank, heal or pull, but I can cope with anything else.   <br /> <br />[edit: 2 more thoughts:  horse in outdoor zones = more medding seconds = more mana.  Also I crit a couple of times, which can take me to 1900 damage for an 8 second spell.  Oh yes, and pulling times are good for medding in.] <br /> <br />This group that has a mob in camp 10 minutes out of 11 - they don't stop to loot?  Or divide loot?  Or talk?  And I take it they run home... <br /> <br />Finally I would agree with bards having the best all-round capabilities.  Again, people who don't often play with bards don't realise just what they can do.  I think Bards have the hardest stun to resist in the game.  They have selos for a quick escape at max speed or a run to Dulak/Nadox.  They get a nice song which gives the party + 40 I think to Dex and makes everyone's weapons proc a lot... I have fought in POJ with a bard as the healer and SK as tank and a monk, and we killed non-stop.  You need to handle it differently, but it can be done.  And of course, clerics and casters like the bard, for mana regen songs. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sun Apr 17 06:41:18 2005 by Sianu</span></i></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Sorceress Sianu Starbright <br />Guild Reporter, High Eastern Erudites <br />Antonius Bayle <br /> <br />"Whether you think you can, or whether you think you can't, you're right."</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from England</td></tr></table>
